p: Mosquitoes were collected as eggs or adults from several locations in Queensland. Adult Ae. vigilax, Ae. procax, Cx. annulirostris and Cx. sitiens were collected using Centers for Disease Control light traps (Model 512, John Hock Co., Gainesville, FL) baited with CO 2 (1kg dry ice) from several suburbs in Brisbane, southeastern Queensland. Adult mosquitoes were transported to the laboratory and exposed to ZIKV within 5 h of collection.
